-- PAs (as-pattern): the as-variable binds the WHOLE scrutinee; the inner
-- pattern binds its own vars.  Exercises bindPattern's PAs arm: `p@(a,b)` binds
-- `p` to the tuple AND destructs it into `a`/`b`.  This fixture only uses `a`/`b`
-- (not `p`), so it tests that the inner descent works.  Reduces to 34.
main = match (3, 4)
  p@(a, b) => a * 10 + b
